<HEADLINE>
KAOHSIUNG GRANTS DISCOUNT TO LESS PRIVILEGED HOMEBUYERS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaohsiung, June 1 (CNA) 06/01/07  19:30:46 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The Kaohsiung city government announced Friday that its public
housing plan for the less privileged will be extended to cover
physically or mentally disabled and low-income residents.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the city government pointed out that the plan,
launched three years ago, has been granting a 20 percent discount
to single-parent families that buy public housing units and that
Mayor Chen Chu has decided to allow low- income families and
residents with physical or mental disabilities to enjoy the same
privilege.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that from June 1, less privileged people can
apply to buy housing units in five different locations, provided
they have been residents in Kaohsiung for one year.
</P>
<P>
He added that eligible applicants are entitled to 30-year low-
interest loans, in addition to other benefits including paying
their downpayments in 24 installments interest-free and a
mortgage rate at 2.86 percent per annum for NT$2.2 million of the
loan.
</P>
<P>
Information about the housing plan can be viewed by accessing the
city government's  Urban  Development  Bureau  Web  site  at
http://urban- web.kcg.gov.tw.
</P>
